INSERT INTO `t_blog` VALUES (57, 4, 'Supernote', 'The history of electronic paper', '<p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/632c8014-6ec1-404f-807b-1364cc833825.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=bYZbTs4zWPfP0TGpg94GEYId5Dc%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">In 2007, Amazon released the first generation of e-reader Kindle, which is</span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">equipped with a 6-inch 4th-order electronic paper ink screen.With the</span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">popularity of the Kindle, e-paper is truly familiar to consumers.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Electronic Paper (ePaper) is a display technology that mimics the visual</span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">perception of printing and writing on paper.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/2b0f8cdc-e954-4b17-8f63-0d0c4fa1cfb8.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=V53dfMiPAALrNjjGLa3OmKDOXF0%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Unlike ordinary flat panel displays that display images with illuminating </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">light, electronic papers use electrophoresis display (EPD) as a display </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">panel. They rely on reflected ambient light to display images, which are </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">more comfortable to read and can display images.It is still clearly visible </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">under direct sunlight, and has a wide viewing angle, theoretically up to </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">180 degrees.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">E-paper is flexible and low-power, and is widely used in reading and </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">writing, mobile wear, electronic shelf labels, electronic signage, </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">architecture and design.</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/dd52b8f8-6080-4db4-a359-d933ef60d785.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=0o5ysvGxgrhOpIuYDo799dhI4h8%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">However, looking back on the past, the development of electronic paper </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">has also encountered many crises.From the birth of the 1960s to the real </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">large-scale application at the beginning of this century, e-paper has </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">experienced many difficulties and obstacles.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">In the era of LCD technology, how did e-paper break through?</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><h2>Electronic paper or LCD screen? Panasonicâ€™s hesitation</h2><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">The first electronic paper in history was not from E Ink, but a famous </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Japanese electrical appliance company, Panasonic.</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/8cdf29ca-10de-44da-8afd-9ff8fc3c7942.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=fG67uVsAzYJeeo6zFxybg%2FOmpeg%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">In 1968, the Radio Corporation of America (RCA) published the theory that </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">â€œdisplays can be made using liquid crystal materials.â€ This theory later </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">became the basis for the development of liquid crystal panels.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">At the time, å¤ªç”°å‹‹å¤«, who developed the electronic photo display liquid, </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">was shocked when he heard the news. He immediately started researching </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">it. After the research, he boldly came to the conclusion that electrophoresis </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">technology is more promising than liquid crystal technology in display </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">applications.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">å¤ªç”°å‹‹å¤« began to develop electrophoretic electronic paper. In 1969, he </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">applied for several patents related to electrophoresis technology.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">In the 1970s, Panasonic began to market its products.At the same time, </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">another electronic paper technology â€œGyriconâ€ was born in 1970. It was </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">developed by the famous Xerox Palo Alto Research Center, where the </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">mouse, laser printer, graphical user interface and page description </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">language Interpress were born.Major inventions that affect the historical </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">process of the 20th century.</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/453fd73d-c357-4d10-88e3-d435ede4708b.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=iB9PjkJc1vaOvprdz5anA2H6dUs%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">However, the good times did not last long. In 1976, Panasonic suddenly </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">chose to stop developing electronic paper and turned to the LCD screen </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">field.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">It may be because the product repair rate at that time was extremely high, </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">and it may be due to the envy of the Sharp LCD display calculator.</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/85c5199d-8dc6-4613-81a3-760ba32991cb.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=7YCk1eBIGVYXShmVmryiRo68w0Y%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">From the perspective of interests, Panasonicâ€™s choice may be right. After </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">several decades, LCD monitors have brought huge gains to Panasonic.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">However, the development of electronic paper has thus stagnate, and </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Xeroxâ€™s Gyricon has only lived in the laboratory.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Will e-paper be going to fail?</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><h2>The development of electronic paper technology, the birth of E Ink</h2><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">It was not until the 1990s that after 20 years of decadence, electronic paper </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">finally ushered in spring.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">In 1995, in the MIT Media Lab, Professor Neil Gershenfeld, physicist </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Joseph Jacobson, mathematics student Barrett Comiskey, and mechanical </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">engineering student JD Albert co-created E Ink.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Electrophoretic ink technology is commonly known as electronic ink.The </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">electronic ink is coated on a layer of plastic film, and then attached to a </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">thin film transistor (TFT) circuit, and controlled by a driver IC to form a </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">pixel pattern to create an electronic paper display (EPD).</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/6bb11760-cac7-481d-8af3-710010ef5384.png?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=9w546qDUi02F6x4fu6%2FKMzz8cCI%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">They then applied for a patent and in 1997 they teamed up to create the E </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Ink company.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Since then, electronic paper has begun to enter the publicâ€™s field of vision.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><h2>The road to commercialization of electronic paper, E Ink dominates</h2><h2>the field of electronic paper</h2><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Through the wave of e-ink technology, in May 1999, E Ink launched an </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">outdoor e-paper called Immedia for advertising.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">However, what really caused a sensation was the â€œe-newspaperâ€ </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">conceptual model launched by IBM in the same year.</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/fac79bab-a66f-49ee-9cbf-b12b764274ca.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=HHprhnQygEP9darMi9CCDwDbqfY%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">In 1999, at the largest newspaper exhibition in the United States, IBM </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">demonstrated an â€œe-newspaperâ€ that could read text and image </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">information through an electronic display layer, attracting attention from </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">the newspaper publishing industry around the world.The New York Times </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">and The Washington Post spoke highly of the â€œe-newspaperâ€, claiming that </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">this e-reading has revolutionary significance, and BusinessWeek also </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">awarded the annual IDEA American Industrial Design Award to the </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">â€œElectronic Newspaper.â€In recognition of its cross-age value in terms of </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">printing cost savings and news timeliness.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/932e7b4c-016d-4ca5-80e3-c46c9d36e773.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=LE7an50rlyzeJa1Hegez6cjwFRg%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Robert Steinbugler, who is the chief designer of IBM and the head of the </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">â€œelectronic newspaperâ€ project, proudly said: â€œPeople will be able to see the </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">part of the newspaper that they are most interested in anytime and anywhere, and </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">the electronic newspaper will be spread all over the world.â€</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">However, at that time, the development of the network had not reached </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">the level that could support this idea. The â€œelectronic newspaperâ€ </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">eventually became the fantasy of IBM.However, it seems now that the </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">concept of customized information flow contained in the â€œelectronic </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">newspaperâ€ happens to be the focus of competition among major Internet </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">giants in more than a decade.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">IBMâ€™s â€œfailureâ€ did not delay the development of e-paper. From 00 to 2002, </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">new technologies such as curled e-paper and color e-paper were </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">introduced.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">In 2004, the road to commercialization of electronic paper finally ushered </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">in a historic breakthrough, and Sony once again became a pioneer in the </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">industry.</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/ea262913-d985-4288-b7d8-fe8e37bdc848.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=PCyQrdmPN%2B8d8KXn64gd1Zx9J4M%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">The worldâ€™s first commercially available electronic paper â€œLIBRIeâ€, </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">powered by Eink and Philips, was produced by Sony.The LIBRIe measures </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">190Ã—126Ã—13mm and weighs only 190g. It only needs 4 batteries and 7 </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">batteries to browse 10,000 pages. The careful Sony also provides users </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">with 4 kinds of contrast adjustment and recording functions also joined by </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Sony to LIBRIe.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">The launch of the electronic paper of 40,000 yen has attracted worldwide </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">attention and, more importantly, it has led to new developments in the </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">electronic paper industry.</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/018421f1-a845-451d-a375-379149415cf7.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=3j2EIJHnlk2V%2FiPpyyF1lM4GhRg%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Electronic companies around the world are rushing to develop e-paper </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">products, and they are aware of the huge potential of the e-paper market.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">In 2005, Seiko released the first electronic ink watch called Spectrum </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">SVRD001, which looks like a crafted bracelet that uses the softness of </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">electronic paper to make it extremely thin and low-power design effect.</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/e50d1287-5b77-4812-8566-a3687205cf49.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=QnJ3V6Zsxz6mF55gA%2FEbevp%2FbKc%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">In 2007, Amazon released the first generation of e-reader Kindle. What </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Amazon didnâ€™t expect was that this e-ink screen product was sold out for </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">five hours after it was sold. Amazon will not be able to resume supply until </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">several months laterã€‚</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/36215c56-cef5-420d-959e-3676ea24af30.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=kByQfPxmgRFI2WjgfWHi9p0iEAk%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">On June 1, 2009, E Ink announced that it will be acquired by its major </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">business partner Yuan Tai for more than US$400 million, which has </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">accelerated the development of electronic paper technology.And, by 2012, </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">E Ink acquired SiPix, one of only a few competitors.</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/b3cbb687-1348-4b85-8a03-2c358ac4f1ea.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=FNUS8qFdSk1vNvdkCv2aV9oguek%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">By this time, most of the electronic paper products used E Inkâ€™s </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">technology.With about 90% of the electronic paper market share, E Ink </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">finally established the â€œelectronic paperâ€ empire.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><h2>The impact of the IPAD? Electronic paper goes its own way</h2><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">E Ink looks to the farther future, but this road will not be smooth.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">In the early morning of January 28th, 2010, Steve Jobs, who was slightly </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">gaunt, stood on the podium of the Yerba Buena Art Center in San </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Francisco: â€œApple will bring you a revolutionary new productâ€¦ its size is </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">between IPHONE and MACBOOK.In the meantime, it can watch videos, </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">listen to music, play games, read e-booksâ€¦ the experience it brings will be </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">unprecedented.â€</span></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">The first generation of IPAD was presented to the world and opened the </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">curtain of modern tablet computers.The color display and video fluency </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">brought by the LCD panel are unmatched by electronic paper, and there </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">will be more and more tablet terminal devices equipped with LCD screens </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">in the future.Later, the IPAD even added a stylus.</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/48e00b0b-da4c-4951-9a16-11d65da2d057.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=TrVJfohZDAGv3jfpSVqipBwea78%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">The industry is worried, can the electronic paper market develop </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">smoothly?</span></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">At the crossroads, E Ink resolutely chose to stick to his own path and take </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">advantage of the unique features of e-paper.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Maybe you didnâ€™t notice that e-paper has been used in every corner.</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/6d43c485-8ed7-4c04-84d3-0b610aee37f2.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=MhpM3V0KsHIxiuU3j6aZfA8LVxg%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">Some bus stop signs have been equipped with electronic paper screens, </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">which display bus line information in real time and can be charged by solar </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">energy.</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/f6bad7cb-65de-4645-a7f9-5896201a87bb.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=t7FMqXd3tYB4R9mYzZ030%2B9xcjY%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">This is the e-paper label in the retail store, which can change the price </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">information at any time, especially for fresh foods with large seasonal </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">changes, which can reduce the waste of a large amount of </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">ingredients.E-paper labels can reduce paper printing, low cost, low power </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">consumption, battery life can be used for more than 5 years, and because of </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">the non-viewing characteristics of e-paper, the shelves from the top to the </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">bottom can be seen at all.It is still clearly visible under strong light.</span></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/53c3b702-b8d0-42c6-b9f5-29a3cf2051c3.png?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=ncAR05EkxmbLas0AkKsUwvAvQKg%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">This is an electronic paper whiteboard from QuirkLogic, a high-contrast 42-</span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">inch screen with an ultra-wide viewing angle that displays content as comfortable as </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">real paper, touch-handwriting is very smooth, and has </span></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">networking capabilities.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><img src=\"https://test-cms.cn-sh2.ufileos.com/c6621d04-f6d7-4afe-bf8e-02fbd56bcdfb.jpg?UCloudPublicKey=rDlR5TKlbJ9czJLkJrNttUfkJaudoVi%2Br%2BSksVk3XFKjvmr2ue%2Fyc%2FuO2TdhyBpo&amp;Expires=&amp;Signature=2t3UCiNxprNFBIZAs3aXyPYVuQU%3D\"></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span class=\"ql-size-large\">The ParceLive e-paper logistics label can display information such as the </span></p><p><span c